                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d579">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 855.48/799b</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_LIB1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Laughlin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-19T15:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 19, 1918, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2302. For <persName corresp="#p_PWB1">Poland</persName> from <persName
                        corresp="#p_HHC1">Hoover</persName>:</p>
                <p>For your own information and for reasons will communicate later, Belgian
                    Government may ask and it may be insisted by American <pb facs="0575" n="491"
                        xml:id="pg_491"/> Government that C.R.B. continue through reconstruction
                    period. If so, will ask have all relations precisely defined by President.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
